    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah i know a bit, but i'm kinda worried about it. the stuff we were doing with the main character's psychological depth and those darker, more realistic grit elements... the new template basically kills all of that. it's gonna make the writing way more bland and \"safe.\" it feels like we're gonna lose the soul of the story. do u think there's any way to keep the depth without triggering the compliance flags?",
